<item>
            <title>[LU-19484] FLR-EC: Add lfs ec resync and lfs ec verify commands</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19484</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Implement new user-space commands to create and verify EC parity data:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lfs ec resync &#8212; generates/regenerrates parity data for an existing EC file &amp;amp; writes it to EC components&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lfs ec verify &#8212; reads back and validates parity data against the source data.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both commands will use the designated EC read/write functionality introduced in the previous ticket to perform direct I/O to the parity components.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to consider the relationship between erasure coding and mirrors here. &#160;Probably, the resync operation can annotate which components it actually resync&apos;ed and that should take care of it&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
